{"title":"The Sentence","author":{"name":"Anna Akhmatova"},"publishDate":"2009-01-05","lines":[{"line":"And the stone word fell","stanza":1,"number":1},{"line":"On my still-living breast.","stanza":1,"number":2},{"line":"Never mind, I was ready.","stanza":1,"number":3},{"line":"I will manage somehow.","stanza":1,"number":4},{"line":"Today I have so much to do:","stanza":2,"number":5},{"line":"I must kill memory once and for all,","stanza":2,"number":6},{"line":"I must turn my soul to stone,","stanza":2,"number":7},{"line":"I must learn to live again—","stanza":2,"number":8},{"line":"Unless…Summer’s ardent rustling","stanza":3,"number":9},{"line":"Is like a festival outside my window.","stanza":3,"number":10},{"line":"For a long time I’ve foreseen this","stanza":3,"number":11},{"line":"Brilliant day, deserted house.","stanza":3,"number":12}]}